          <p class='first-para'>
            No. If someone has just joined&#x2014;if they do not yet have vested rights&#x2014;at the moment they are entitled to take out their cash payment. The sums are tiny, in which case the compensation would apply to the level of money that they would otherwise have got. They would be bought out, so to speak. If instead they prefer to keep the money as a pension payment, they would get 90 per cent of that and choose whatever was greater.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0664P0-05082'>
        <a name='S5LV0664P0_20040909_GCR_118'>  </a>
