            <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_225gc' title='Col. 225GC &mdash; HL Deb 09 September 2004 vol 664 c225GC' name='column_225gc' href='#column_225gc' rel='bookmark'>225GC</a>
            scheme where pension funds are paying in and are effectively being insured against the risk of disaster. That is what most people think it is and it is what I believe it is in practice. The harder it is to envisage such an apocalypse happening&#x2014;as I mentioned, Mr Wicks was talking about it yesterday&#x2014;the more convinced we are that this let-out clause should not be allowed. It is simply that in that situation people need their pensions to be protected.
          </p>
