          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_260gc' title='Col. 260GC &mdash; HL Deb 09 September 2004 vol 664 c260GC' name='column_260gc' href='#column_260gc' rel='bookmark'>260GC</a>
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0664P0-05549'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0664P0_20040909_GCR_585' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        Page 117, line 2, after "consult" insert "the Board and"
      </p>
      
      <p class='procedural' id='S5LV0664P0-05550'>
        <a class='permalink' href='#S5LV0664P0_20040909_GCR_586' title='Link to this contribution' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
        The noble Lord said: We are interested in the two amendments in this group because they cover a situation in which the Secretary of State decides&#x2014;
      </p>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0664P0-05551'>
        <a name='S5LV0664P0_20040909_GCR_587'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/ms-patricia-hollis' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S5LV0664P0_20040909_GCR_587' title='Link to this speech by Ms Patricia Hollis' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/ms-patricia-hollis" title="Ms Patricia Hollis">Baroness Hollis of Heigham</a></cite>
          <p class='first-para'>
            As Amendment No. 259 was not moved, I assumed that neither were Amendments Nos. 266 and 267, which are grouped with it. I was just checking.
          </p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
      
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S5LV0664P0-05552'>
        <a name='S5LV0664P0_20040909_GCR_588'>  </a>
